main_text: Renesas' solar-powered location tracker is a modular asset tracking system featuring wireless connectivity via an LTE Cat-M1/NB-IoT cellular modem. Optionally, Bluetooth®Low Energy (LE) and Wi-Fi connectivity can be supported with additional radios through Pmod™ interfaces. A central MCU manages the system, balancing low power requirements with interface capabilities, performance, and flexibility. The system is powered and charged by photovoltaic (PV) solar cells or a USB Type-C®connection, ensuring efficient and sustainable operation.
benefits: Supports LTE Cat-M1 and NB-IoT 1 and 2 versions for robust cellular connectivity.
Software-assisted GNSS enhances location tracking capabilities.
Wi-Fi and Bluetooth LE support for versatile connectivity options.
Utilizes PV energy harvesting for sustainable power generation.
Unified firmware for various radio configurations.
Flexible power control to adjust to changing conditions.
Full Software Update Over-the-Air (SUOTA) support for seamless firmware updates.
